  "response": "The salary for a Pharma MBA graduate can vary widely depending on several factors:\n\n1. Entry-level positions:\n- Typically range from \u20b94-8 lakhs per annum\n- Can be higher in top pharmaceutical companies\n\n2. Mid-level positions (3-5 years experience):\n- \u20b98-15 lakhs per annum\n- Roles in marketing, sales, business development\n\n3. Senior-level positions (5-10 years experience):\n- \u20b915-25 lakhs per annum\n- Management and strategic roles\n\n4. Factors affecting salary:\n- Company reputation\n- Location\n- Individual performance\n- Specialization\n- Market demand\n\n5. Potential job roles:\n- Product Manager\n- Sales Manager\n- Marketing Manager\n- Business Development Executive\n- Pharmaceutical Consultant\n- Research Analyst\n\n6. Top paying sectors:\n- Multinational pharmaceutical companies\n- Research organizations\n- Healthcare consulting firms\n- Pharmaceutical marketing firms\n\n7. Additional factors:\n- MBA institute's reputation\n- Individual's academic performance\n- Internship and prior work experience\n\nSalaries can be significantly higher in top-tier companies and with exceptional performance.",
